description:
"The Hermit's Ghost Dog!"

Doctor Terrence Thirteen, the Ghost-Breaker, and his companion, Marie, hear screams in the forest, while en route to a lodge. Thirteen, and Marie, discover a man, horribly slaughtered, by some wild animal. Thirteen encounters an old, blind man, Bart Harley, in the forest. Harley blames the death on his dog, Dirk. Harley wanders off, seemingly being guided by his dead guide dog. Speaking with the sheriff, Thirteen learns that three hunters, Carter Blane, Harry Acker, and Marlowe, accidentally killed Dirk, while deer hunting. Ever since, the townsfolk have witnessed Harley, wandering about at night, seemingly guided by his dead dog. Thirteen meets with Acker, and Marlowe, at their hunting lodge. A ward against ghosts has been painted on the door to the lodge.

The police question Harley, testing him to ascertain if he is really blind. Thirteen sets a bear trap on the path from Harley's home. Astonishingly, Harley avoids the trap, seemingly guided away, from the deadly obstacle, by his dead guide dog. Thirteen races to the hunting lodge, but he's too late. Marlowe has already been claimed by the ghost dog. Acker flees, but Thirteen, wearing Acker's clothes, waits for Dirk, in the lodge. Thirteen is fascinated by the eerie glow coming from the fish in the river. Thirteen is attacked by the ghost dog, barely escaping with his life. Desperate to find a rational explanation to the seemingly supernatural occurrences, Thirteen searches the surrounding forest, as well as Harley's cabin.

Thirteen notices his shoes glowing with the same eerie florescence of the fish. Thirteen confronts Acker, who is astonished to see Thirteen alive. Thirteen reveals the glowing coat Acker made for his own hunting dog. The dog that killed Blane, and was sent to kill Thirteen. Acker, Blane, and Marlowe had discovered a fortune in radioactive material, in the stream outside their hunting lodge. Acker, using Harley's threats of Dirk's vengeance from beyond the grave, murdered Blane and Marlowe, to keep the profits, from their discovery, for himself. Thirteen reveals that Harley suffers from an affliction that allows him to see at night, though he is still blind during the day. Harley's crazed mind, unable to comprehend the incongruity of his affliction, has deluded himself into believing that he is still guided, at night, by Dirk.

description:
Hang on to your hair piece! It's Big Guy a go-go! Mike Allred introduces the latest addition to the Legend line-up in this thunderous two-part story pitting Frank Miller and Geof Darrow's Big Guy against Snap City's super-sensation, Madman! Madman's mad-scientist buddy, Dr. Boiffard, is suffering from an ever-expanding brain that's soaking up information like a roll of quilted Bounty. The American government figures Boiffard's got one valuable load of headcheese so it sends its golden retriever, The Big Guy, to reel in the big fish! Can Madman stop the ten-foot tall, twelve-hundred-pound armory from kidnapping his old buddy?! What doesn't kill him makes him sore for weeks!

Frank Miller does The Big Guy's dialogue; Geof Darrow draws the mechanical monolith on the cover.
name: Big Guy A Go-Go

description: Staple your butt to your Lazy Boy and grab a twelve-pack of Jolt! We've got a thirty-two page nuclear blast we're calling Big Brain-o-rama! Catch the thrilling conclusion to the cataclysmic Madman/Big Guy crossover, as the two twisted titans run a gun-toting gauntlet of rival renegade robots in their quest to get Dr. Boiffard and his ever-expanding gray matter into the protective hands of special agent Chow Skip Wang! Will they make it in time, or will Boiffard go kablooey?!! It's Madman mayhem at its mayhemiest, with a Big Guy bonanza thrown in for a bonus!
name: Big, Mad Brainarama

name: Volume 6

description: The new miniseries illuminating Gotham City continues! As a new Gotham rises, one madman threatens to tear it apart. His name is Purge, and his relentless attacks have thrown this new "City of Light" into chaos. And the one man who can save the day - the dark avenger who has always fought to save Gotham - is losing himself in an intense internal battle. Can Batman pull himself together?

The miniseries presenting a Gotham City bathed in light continues! Batman slips further into self-annihilation, as he tries in vain to deal with a death he could not prevent. Meanwhile, Batgirl is forced to take his place as the dark avenger of Gotham City. But can she ? or anyone ? save a Gotham without Batman?

Consumed by his own demons, Batman struggles to hold his fractured psyche together as he faces the deadly Purge. But even as Batgirl and the Gotham City Police Department close in on the melee, Purge threatens to annihilate the Dark Knight!

Batgirl battles Purge, with Gotham City at stake! Meanwhile, Allen and Montoya search vainly for Angela in the insane expanse of Tower One and Batman disappears into the primordial abyss of his own soul...

The penultimate chapter of the engrossing miniseries! Purge has kidnapped another victim, and Tower One threatens to smash Detectives Allen and Montoya to smithereens. Can Batman keep his crumbling psyche together long enough to save them all?
Reprints Ultimate Spider-Man #72-85.
name: Volume 7

description: Chapter one of eight - A transferred police officer, Lt. Cheri Major, heads the Rankor Island Police (R.I.P.) Violent Messiahs task force, targeting the island's murderous vigilantes, Citizen Pain and Family Man.

description: This black and white issue introduces the Violent Messiahs protagonists and acts as a prologue to the story. The series was picked up by Image after this first issue.

description:
Chapter 2 of 4
 Thrown too soon into a new investigation an unstable Lieutenant Cheri Major is led into Scalpel's dimly lit world of control and submission. Never more alone than now, our protagonist hangs bound in the dark,  
Scalpel's prisoner. Here Cheri will learn that she and the mysterious killer have something in common, an obsession with the now legendary vigilante Citizen Pain.

The adventures of the turn of the century Shadowman, Maxim St. James, chronicled at last! Danger awaits as a Shadowman goes abroad, with an adventure in merry old blighty side by side with the immortal Armstrong, bare knuckle prize fights, high tech airships, steam powered cars, and a colonialist English necromancer!

Did not ship until Jan. 1995.

description:
The voodoo hounfor that created the Shadowman comes to reclaim the power from Mike LeRoi. But stripped of the Mask of Shadows, the one-time hitman formerly known only as Zero is still a force to be reckoned with. Something that the Horses of Carnage are going to find out when Mike comes gunning for them.

Variant cover: Glow in the dark (see pic below).
name: Rebirth, Part 1

description: Art for the first few issues was taken from the daily newspaper, strip with the same name started in the early 30’s, by famed American illustrator Harrison Cady (1877-1970), which is why the comic has such an old fashion look even though it started in 1947, in the fifties however everything was changed with Peter becoming a “cow-boy rabbit” and only the numbering staying the same.
name: Peter Rabbit Comics

description: Looking for clues to finding his kidnapped lover, Shadowman is drawn into the Deadside vortex that is the Vietnam memorial. If you thought that jungle conflict was ugly, wait until you see the Deadside version. And if that weren't enough, some powerful people in the Alignment are trying to tap into the very heart of Deadside, causing Shadowman...problems. And who is the man called Blacktower?
name: A Tale of Two Kings

description: All right, just about now, Shadowman's really looking to stop, regroup, maybe settle back with a beer. Tough. Mysterious figures seek to steal Claudine away from him (and she just got back from Deadside!). But these attackers are far more than they appear. It's a journey to Deadside like you've never seen before!
name: Serpent's Tooth

description: Shadowman won't rest until he's captured Mah, and rescued Claudine! Ok, maybe he will. Too bad he's picked the quiet little town of Alvader, Georgia to look for our favorite psycho murderess. They're not too thrilled that Zero's taking a break in their town, and it's not because he's bald.
name: Skin Trade

description: Zero struggles with recollections of his life as Mike LeRoi before Shadowman while the unquiet corpse of Jack Boniface stalks him looking to reclaim the Shadowman power for itself!
name: Rebirth, Part 2

description:
On the borderlands of life and death, Shadowman - the voodoo guardian of the barriers between the worlds - continues his deadly struggle to protect Earth from the evil denizens of Deadside. MIchael Leroi, D.J. and mystical voodoo warrior is given this almost impossible task.

Variants exist:

- Limited variant cover given one for every five copies ordered. (see pic 2)

- No cover price - giveaway in video stores at the same time as 1999 Shadowman game was released. (see pic 3)
name: Mission Unspeakable

description:
What do you get when a violent gang of undead zombies, a sexy blonde, a talking chicken, and graffiti that comes to life all decide to show up and rain on your parade? Well, you get all hell breaking loose. Shadowman handles these problem the only way he knows how. With his pistols cocked.

Limited variant (see pic 2) given one for every five copies ordered.
name: Law And Order

description:
Legion and his cabal of serial killers begin their scheme to bring the corruption of the Deadside to Earth. And only Shadowman can stop them. However, Legion has other ideas. He has kidnapped the unsuspecting Astrid, hoping to use her as a trap for our hero.

Unity 2000 Prelude - Part One.
name: Asylum Seeker

description:
Shadowman heads into Deadside to rescue Astrid from the evil clutches of Legion and the Asylum!

Unity 2000 prelude - Part 2.
name: Soul Survivor

description: A blood feud between vampire gangs of New Orleans leads Shadowman into the garden of good and evil...and into a head-on confrontation with an ancient frenzied force known only as "The Thirst."
name: A Twist Of Lemon

description: The oldest and most debauched party is coming the Big Easy, and Shadowman will be there to meet it.
name: Masquerade Part One

description: The first romance comic, created by Simon & Kirby and published by Prize it was later bought by DC.
name: Young Romance

description:
Kid tries to help out a guy who has a horrid wife, and he`s too meek to stand against her.

Kid calls for four historical ones, but they can`t help.

After calling for Bluebeard to scare the wife, things get worse. Beard knocks the heroes out, and gives the husband this advice: She gets difficult, wack her.

This he does. Our heroes find this out, because the dead wife tells about it, when she gets to Heaven.

The heroic pair go to take him to justice.

There`s a fierce fight, and then the man kills himself, so he wont have to go to jail.

All three go to Heaven, and the man is fine with how everything turned out.

Up until his dead wife starts to nag again.
Chapter 3 of 4
Chapter 4 of 4

Chapter 2 of 8 
 
Cheri's night in hell isn't over yet.She has seen Citizen Pain. Like a demon in the flames, he trapped her and spoke to her. His voice was dark and sizzling, and it said that her life would never be the same, again. Cheri Major, some hero. She's plagued by nightmares, caught in politics and fending off the sexual advances of a smart-ass detective. For the first time in her life she feels as though she's lost control. That's too bad . . . because the VIOLENT MESSIAHS have only just begun to raise hell.
name: Book of Job, Chapter 2

description: He is in her home. The man that Cheri Major has sworn to destroy, Citizen Pain, has skulked around in the shadows of her dreams for months. Now he's here, in the flesh, holding her at gunpoint, in the one place where she is suppose to feel the most safe, her own home. What will he do to her? What message will he impart? Cheri's struggle to make the connection between the serial killer "Family Man" and the vigilante Citizen Pain continues. A truth is revealed through brutal confrontation, a single truth that only deepens the mystery.
name: Book of Job, Chapter 3

description: Cheri Major is caught in the middle of a violent struggle between the enigmatic monster Citizen Pain and the golden boy serial killer Jeremiah Parker. Tonight begins a descent into uncertainty and chaos. The next three issues of Violent Messiahs will take place in one nightmarish evening. It's a survivalist marathon 'till dawn and the creators haven't even introduced you to the real bad guys yet.
name: Book of Job, Chapter 4

description:
Chapter 5 of 8 
 
In Cheri's desperate quest to capture Citizen Pain she has seen him burst through walls, take bullets and disappear into thin air. What manner of man could control such an indestructible monster? The frail ancient wheelchair bound Jubal? Hardly... prepare yourself, the KEEPERS of Pain have arrived.
name: Book of Job, Chapter 5

description:
Chapter 6 of 8 
 
"Tonight The Door Opens" Citizen Pain, the soldier puppet of a darkly laid conspiracy, has never committed an act of free will in his entire life. That's all about to change. Tonight his love for Cheri will give him the courage to breach the mysterious threshold at the center of the house, forcing a violent confrontation with the very men who command him. PLUS -- LOW TRIBE PREVIEW! An alien planet hosts three distinct primitive species, those who fly, those who build, and those who dig. Now a massive digger beast has been cast out from the belly of the Earth because of his friendship with a frail grounded child flyer. Together they will take an epic journey on the brutal surface and challenge the social order of their civilization. Survival rests in the very emotional bond that has ostracized them. Joshua Dysart (writer/co-creator of Violent Messiahs) and new comer Rick Morales give you a glimpse of a wholly original sequential art experience in their 5 page flip-book preview, LOW TRIBE. A New World awaits.
name: Book of Job, Chapter 6

description:
Chapter 7 of 8 
 
IN THE FINAL STRETCH! They told us, "An eight issue story arc is too long!"... Man were they wrong. Violent Messiahs has relied heavily on its serialized novel structure to steadily pull its readers from the realism of issue #1's gritty city streets to the sci-fi nightmare of issue #6. And with every step our readership has grown. Now, because it's about damn time, we begin our conclusion. Our players clash. Men rage against genetic destiny. Cheri and Houston struggle simply to stay sane. Everyone has a gun. Nuff' said. Issue #7, the beginning of the end.
name: Book of Job, Chapter 7

description:
Chapter 8 of 8 
 
CONCLUSION! We've toyed with you long enough! All roads lead to North End Mansion for our fiery finale. Love has given Citizen Pain the strength to rebel against the genetic program that controls him and those who have created him. It is in the midst of this monster's personal liberation that Cheri, Houston, Jeremiah, Jubal and the Keepers will collide. Violent Messiahs, the comic book that refuses to follow the rules, brings you the end of its first story arc, an ending that will have you wondering, "where can they possibly go from here?" You think this is just hype!? You must not know us very well. Buckle up, because we're going to make you love comic books all over again.
name: Book of Job, Chapter 8
School for Crime

description: The last appearence of Midnight until 1984 and Roy Thomas' use of him in All-Star Squandron at DC.

name: A Deadly Paradox

description: From a long lost world comes two new citizens to New York: Ziggy Pig and Silly Seal! Unfortunately for them, while they've been living the easy life of cartoon characters, their arch-nemesis Toughy Cat has been living in the real world, and gaining immense power! What used to be all fun and games is now deadly serious! Luckily, when Johnny runs across the desperate duo, the Fantastic Four agree to provide a new life, and protection, for Ziggy and Silly, but can even the Fantastic Four stand against a nigh invulnerable feline fury?!!
name: A Timely Family Appearance
